OL,3,CFuneral directors' 'unduly lenient'
OL,4,Cprison sentence referred to Court of
OL,5,CAppeal
OL,7,FThe prison sentences of two Hampshire
OL,8,Ffuneral directors who were jailed for
OL,9,Ffour years for storing bodies in
OL,10,Funrefrigerated conditions have been
OL,11,Freferred by the solicitor general to
OL,12,Fthe Court of Appeal over concerns they
OL,13,Fwere unduly lenient.
OL,15,FRichard Elkin, 49, and Hayley Bell,
OL,16,F42, who ran Elkin and Bell Funerals in
OL,17,FGosport, were convicted of public
OL,18,Fnuisance, preventing the decent burial
OL,19,Fof a body and fraud offences following
OL,20,Fa trial at Portsmouth Crown Court.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
